wasm-posix-kernel — Licensing
=============================

This project uses a split license model, similar to Linux kernel + musl libc:

  - The platform (kernel, host runtime, SDK, build scripts, examples) is
    licensed under the GNU General Public License, version 2 or later
    (GPL-2.0-or-later). See COPYING for the full text.

  - The runtime library components that are linked into user programs
    (musl-overlay/ and glue/) are licensed under the MIT License.
    See COPYING.runtime for the full text.

This means you can compile and run your own programs — including proprietary
ones — on this platform without the GPL applying to your code. The runtime
library code that gets linked into your program (the syscall glue and libc
overlay) is MIT-licensed, and the kernel communicates with your program via
IPC, not linking.

If you modify the platform itself (kernel, host, SDK), those modifications
are covered by the GPL.


Component Licenses
------------------

GPL-2.0-or-later:
  crates/          Rust kernel and shared types
  host/            TypeScript host runtime
  sdk/             Cross-compilation toolchain wrappers
  scripts/         Build and test scripts
  examples/        Example programs and browser demos

MIT:
  musl-overlay/    Architecture overlay for musl libc (matches musl's license)
  glue/            Syscall glue compiled into user programs


Third-Party Software
--------------------

musl libc — Copyright (c) 2005-2020 Rich Felker, et al.
Licensed under the MIT License. See musl/COPYRIGHT for full details.

The examples/libs/ directory contains source trees of third-party software
(nginx, PHP, MariaDB, Redis, CPython, Git, GNU coreutils, etc.) which retain
their original licenses. See the license files within each subdirectory.
